title: Matthew Fitzpatrick leads by 1 shot at the British Masters
text:
Matthew Fitzpatrick leads by 1 shot at the British Masters By -   
WOBURN, England (AP) - England’s Matthew Fitzpatrick birdied his final two holes to card a seven-under par round of 64 and lead by one stroke on the first day of the British Masters at Woburn on Thursday. 
The 21-year-old Fitzpatrick made six birdies and an eagle in his opening round to edge ahead of Marc Warren, Lee Slattery, Soren Kjeldsen and Robert Karlsson, who all shot a 65. 
Bridgestone Invitational winner Shane Lowry is two shots behind following a five-under 66, alongside Irish compatriot Padraig Harrington. 
Ian Poulter, who is hosting the tournament at his home course, opened with a three-under 68.
